Cook:<br><br>
You said--<br><br>
&quot;Learned long time ago, I could not control what others though about me, what I though about me was more important.&quot;<br><br>
You know, I thought I had that under my hat until the 'Nam stuff arrived. It was extremely difficult, amd impossible in some cases, to dismiss the destructive words of extraordinarily ignorant people. I guess I was very vulnerable and had abysmally low self esteem, as I look into the past. Now I am beginning to learn what to do with this stuff. Although it will never leave me, I hope to convert it to just bad memories down the road. <br><br>
I really would like to just spit in their eye. But what's the point. Those people were so dumb, I doubt that the passage of time has done anything to improve their IQ's. My anger is there though, and that is a very positive sign.<br><br>
Thanks for the support!<br><br>
